1
00:00:12,110 --> 00:00:12,960
You're done?

2
00:00:25,190 --> 00:00:25,960
By the way,

3
00:00:26,350 --> 00:00:28,350
even if Qing Miao poisoned him
with toad venom,

4
00:00:28,350 --> 00:00:29,710
that doesn't prove

5
00:00:29,710 --> 00:00:31,550
she infected him with blood flukes.

6
00:00:31,568 --> 00:00:33,720
=Cases Between Us=
What if Wu Shichuan caught it himself?

7
00:00:33,744 --> 00:00:36,350
We got the search warrant
for tomorrow, didn't we?

8
00:00:36,710 --> 00:00:38,240
=Episode 4=
We'll find out then.

9
00:00:38,540 --> 00:00:43,900
(Wu's Residence)

10
00:00:44,350 --> 00:00:45,600
For the past six months,

11
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:48,200
Master stayed
in the concubine's courtyard.

12
00:00:48,640 --> 00:00:49,880
She personally took care of

13
00:00:49,880 --> 00:00:52,390
his meals and daily needs.

14
00:00:52,496 --> 00:00:53,790
While the concubine was pregnant,

15
00:00:53,790 --> 00:00:55,030
did anything unusual happen?

16
00:00:55,030 --> 00:00:56,320
I was by her side

17
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:57,600
the whole time.

18
00:00:57,840 --> 00:00:59,000
Nothing out of the ordinary.

19
00:01:12,430 --> 00:01:12,950
Chief,

20
00:01:12,950 --> 00:01:13,950
we searched everywhere.

21
00:01:13,950 --> 00:01:15,400
There's nothing useful,

22
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:17,310
except for a toad inside this jar.

23
00:01:24,480 --> 00:01:26,120
This drawer seems
to have a false bottom.

24
00:01:26,310 --> 00:01:27,640
It looks shallower than the others.

25
00:01:33,120 --> 00:01:34,480
Prescription Records?

26
00:01:37,070 --> 00:01:38,000
These should all be

27
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:38,920
Gu Xishan's patients.

28
00:01:40,870 --> 00:01:41,680
The account books.

29
00:01:43,392 --> 00:01:45,230
The pharmaceutical company's
financial records.

30
00:01:47,120 --> 00:01:49,040
The factory was established
the year before last.

31
00:01:49,510 --> 00:01:51,070
The same year Gu Xishan
got into trouble.

32
00:01:54,350 --> 00:01:55,560
Wu Shichuan.

33
00:01:55,870 --> 00:01:57,280
I remember my father mentioning

34
00:01:57,312 --> 00:01:59,760
that my brother-in-law had invested
in a factory with someone.

35
00:02:02,350 --> 00:02:04,350
The largest shareholder is...

36
00:02:05,380 --> 00:02:06,980
(Wu Tong)

37
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:10,080
President Wu Tong of St. Anton Hospital.

38
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:13,000
Wasn't he the witness
in Gu Xishan's case?

39
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:14,280
If Qing Miao kept these,

40
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:15,120
they could be evidence

41
00:02:15,120 --> 00:02:16,430
that they framed Gu Xishan.

42
00:02:16,512 --> 00:02:19,080
That pharmaceutical company
might even be connected to blood flukes.

43
00:02:22,020 --> 00:02:23,020
(St. Anton Hospital)

44
00:02:23,030 --> 00:02:23,710
Chief Yuan,

45
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,590
I've told you many times.

46
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:27,650
(President's Office)
President Wu really is in Tianjin

47
00:02:27,660 --> 00:02:28,520
attending a conference.

48
00:02:28,520 --> 00:02:29,910
His car's parked outside.

49
00:02:30,064 --> 00:02:32,570
If you're going to make up
an excuse, at least make it believable.

50
00:02:32,592 --> 00:02:33,560
If you don't believe me,

51
00:02:33,776 --> 00:02:35,000
there's nothing I can do.

52
00:02:43,220 --> 00:02:45,460
(President's Office)

53
00:02:50,910 --> 00:02:52,080
That old man

54
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:54,310
is stalling us.

55
00:02:56,528 --> 00:02:57,710
Let's wait a little longer.

56
00:02:57,824 --> 00:02:59,712
If he still doesn't show,
we'll arrest him first.

57
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,240
What are you doing here?

58
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,560
Cao's here.

59
00:03:09,470 --> 00:03:10,120
Chief Yuan.

60
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:11,960
Young Master Zhao.

61
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:12,840
Chief Cao,

62
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:14,360
what brings you here?

63
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,470
Transferred to Division Four?

64
00:03:15,470 --> 00:03:17,120
Very funny, Young Master Zhao.

65
00:03:17,470 --> 00:03:18,470
It's the commissioner.

66
00:03:18,910 --> 00:03:21,080
He sent me to relay a message.

67
00:03:26,816 --> 00:03:28,560
"You've only been in the job
for a few days,

68
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:30,750
and you're trying to arrest people
without solid evidence.

69
00:03:30,750 --> 00:03:32,030
Tell them to get back here!"

70
00:03:37,030 --> 00:03:37,910
His exact words.

71
00:03:38,150 --> 00:03:39,120
Not mine.

72
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:39,984
Tell the commissioner

73
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,490
I'm not arresting anyone.
I'll ask a few questions and head back.

74
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,430
Anything else?

75
00:03:49,430 --> 00:03:50,680
He also said

76
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:52,710
I have to bring both of you back,

77
00:03:52,710 --> 00:03:54,240
or I'll be the one in trouble.

78
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,360
Yuan,

79
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:04,000
hear me out,

80
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:04,680
okay?

81
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:07,000
I've been through this before.

82
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,080
Let's not make trouble
on foreign-controlled territory.

83
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:09,710
All right?

84
00:04:09,960 --> 00:04:10,960
This is China.

85
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:13,030
You don't need foreigners
to keep us in line.

86
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:15,630
Stop making things worse.

87
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:16,870
Your father called me.

88
00:04:16,870 --> 00:04:17,680
He wants you home.

89
00:04:18,510 --> 00:04:19,312
Call him back.

90
00:04:19,312 --> 00:04:20,950
Tell him
I'm busy with real business here.

91
00:04:26,720 --> 00:04:27,270
Chief Yuan,

92
00:04:27,870 --> 00:04:29,430
I know you've got powerful backing.

93
00:04:29,472 --> 00:04:30,750
Rules don't seem to matter to you.

94
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:32,430
But when things blow up,

95
00:04:32,656 --> 00:04:33,720
the men in Division Four

96
00:04:34,870 --> 00:04:36,830
will pay the price.

97
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:39,070
They're counting on their paychecks

98
00:04:39,070 --> 00:04:40,630
to support their families.

99
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,720
Think about them for a change.

100
00:04:43,070 --> 00:04:43,630
All right?

101
00:05:07,070 --> 00:05:07,750
Misters,

102
00:05:07,750 --> 00:05:08,750
here are your noodles.

103
00:05:18,992 --> 00:05:20,750
Beijingers take
their zhajiangmian seriously.

104
00:05:21,190 --> 00:05:23,040
The noodles must be hand-pulled,

105
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:23,750
not cut.

106
00:05:23,950 --> 00:05:25,270
And the toppings must include

107
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:26,600
four vegetables.

108
00:05:26,830 --> 00:05:27,510
Shredded cucumber,

109
00:05:27,510 --> 00:05:29,430
radish leaves, bean sprouts,
and chopped celery.

110
00:05:29,430 --> 00:05:30,390
You can't leave any out.

111
00:05:31,904 --> 00:05:34,100
And the sauce should only be about
eighty percent cooked.

112
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:35,510
This place isn't authentic.

113
00:05:35,510 --> 00:05:36,896
I'll make you a proper bowl sometime.

114
00:05:37,070 --> 00:05:38,190
Why are you still here?

115
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,270
Where else would I go?

116
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,160
How would I know that?

117
00:05:47,408 --> 00:05:48,510
My father told me to leave.

118
00:05:48,510 --> 00:05:49,680
It's not like I wanted to.

119
00:05:53,824 --> 00:05:55,360
After you met with Chief Justice Xie,

120
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:56,750
you suddenly backed out.

121
00:05:56,750 --> 00:05:57,390
Why?

122
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:00,120
Chief Justice Xie told me

123
00:06:02,070 --> 00:06:03,630
my brother-in-law might be involved.

124
00:06:03,870 --> 00:06:04,800
The cabinet's full

125
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:06,070
of factional infighting.

126
00:06:06,096 --> 00:06:07,808
I was afraid it might lead back
to my father.

127
00:06:10,360 --> 00:06:11,560
Do you all

128
00:06:12,270 --> 00:06:14,430
think I'm too naive?

129
00:06:19,510 --> 00:06:20,560
At first,

130
00:06:21,800 --> 00:06:22,430
I was worried

131
00:06:22,430 --> 00:06:24,120
you had an ulterior motive.

132
00:06:24,448 --> 00:06:26,190
(South City)
If the people behind this

133
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:27,190
ended up clashing

134
00:06:27,190 --> 00:06:27,950
with my father,

135
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,630
I'd only be making trouble for him.

136
00:06:30,336 --> 00:06:31,310
But later, I realized

137
00:06:31,310 --> 00:06:32,544
you're not that kind of person.

138
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:37,600
You are

139
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:39,190
stubborn.

140
00:06:39,264 --> 00:06:40,160
About Cui Xi's case,

141
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:41,310
I used to think

142
00:06:41,310 --> 00:06:42,630
you had your own agenda.

143
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,310
Who would take

144
00:06:45,070 --> 00:06:46,040
a maid's death seriously?

145
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,720
But you wouldn't let it go.

146
00:06:50,752 --> 00:06:52,000
I've always wanted to ask you.

147
00:06:52,010 --> 00:06:53,810
You could fight these people
until the very end

148
00:06:53,820 --> 00:06:54,944
and still end up with nothing.

149
00:06:57,870 --> 00:06:59,190
Why keep pushing?

150
00:07:04,368 --> 00:07:05,890
Does winning or losing really matter?

151
00:07:07,190 --> 00:07:08,430
What matters

152
00:07:08,430 --> 00:07:10,360
is that even the dead deserve justice,

153
00:07:11,070 --> 00:07:11,750
right?

154
00:07:18,630 --> 00:07:19,870
You really are

155
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:23,310
different from every other cop

156
00:07:23,310 --> 00:07:24,070
I've met.

157
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:33,220
(Volunteers Wanted for Drug Trials)

158
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:35,190
It's a flyer from St. Anton Hospital.

159
00:07:35,750 --> 00:07:36,830
Drug trials?

160
00:07:37,310 --> 00:07:38,870
If the mountain won't come to us,

161
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:42,000
we'll go to the mountain.

162
00:07:42,460 --> 00:07:45,180
(Volunteers Wanted for Drug Trials)

163
00:07:47,630 --> 00:07:48,510
Say that again.

164
00:07:48,864 --> 00:07:49,830
You want me to do what?

165
00:07:50,270 --> 00:07:51,630
Go undercover.

166
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:53,240
Sneak into St. Anton Hospital

167
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,360
and gather evidence.

168
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,560
Covering for you in front of Dad
wasn't enough?

169
00:07:56,912 --> 00:07:58,190
Now I have to risk my life, too?

170
00:07:58,430 --> 00:07:59,800
You won't die.

171
00:08:01,232 --> 00:08:02,070
Young Lady Zhao,

172
00:08:02,112 --> 00:08:02,944
here's the situation.

173
00:08:03,056 --> 00:08:05,280
St. Anton Hospital has been conducting
illegal drug trials.

174
00:08:05,328 --> 00:08:06,750
It causes the blood fluke outbreak.

175
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:08,070
We have to stop them,

176
00:08:08,070 --> 00:08:09,750
or the consequences
will be unimaginable.

177
00:08:14,190 --> 00:08:15,584
Someone told us you used to perform

178
00:08:15,648 --> 00:08:17,072
with your girls' school's drama club.

179
00:08:17,088 --> 00:08:19,040
They said you're an outstanding actress.

180
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:21,072
As an experienced performer,

181
00:08:21,088 --> 00:08:22,430
you should go to the hospital,

182
00:08:22,430 --> 00:08:25,100
join the drug trial, and get us evidence
along with some parasite eggs.

183
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:27,160
Then hand them over
to the police. Namely, me.

184
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:34,870
Forget it.

185
00:08:35,150 --> 00:08:36,030
She's not up for it.

186
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,750
How do you know?

187
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:40,770
Besides shopping and mahjong,
what else can she do?

188
00:08:40,784 --> 00:08:41,990
Don't make things hard for her.

189
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:43,600
Then who do we ask?

190
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:44,120
That's enough.

191
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:44,870
Drop your act.

192
00:08:45,720 --> 00:08:46,960
I can help,

193
00:08:47,790 --> 00:08:48,960
but not for free.

194
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:50,720
What do you want?

195
00:08:52,790 --> 00:08:55,000
That "Ladies of the Jin Dynasty"
painting of yours...

196
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:56,200
You!

197
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:00,600
Deal.

198
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:03,030
If I'm going to survive in this family,

199
00:09:03,030 --> 00:09:04,390
I'll also need a handgun.

200
00:09:04,656 --> 00:09:05,600
You can't give her that.

201
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:06,320
No way.

202
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:06,720
Deal.

203
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:08,270
An imported one. Nice-looking.

204
00:09:08,270 --> 00:09:09,030
No problem.

205
00:09:09,030 --> 00:09:09,910
Luger P08.

206
00:09:09,910 --> 00:09:10,670
Artillery model.

207
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,910
Don't think
about passing me a fake.

208
00:09:12,910 --> 00:09:14,000
I'll have it authenticated.

209
00:09:14,010 --> 00:09:15,990
If it's fake, you owe me
a hundred times its value.

210
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:22,910
You really spoil her.

211
00:09:25,320 --> 00:09:26,080
I spoil her?

212
00:09:28,300 --> 00:09:29,300
(St. Anton Hospital)

213
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:30,320
Everyone, quiet.

214
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:31,320
Line up.

215
00:09:31,630 --> 00:09:32,550
Listen up.

216
00:09:32,750 --> 00:09:35,030
Drink this bottle right here
on the spot.

217
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:37,000
We'll observe you for an hour.

218
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,200
Then you can leave

219
00:09:38,288 --> 00:09:39,360
and come back in a month.

220
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:56,120
What are you doing?

221
00:09:58,240 --> 00:09:59,360
Someone's getting beaten up!

222
00:10:08,030 --> 00:10:09,030
Slow down.

223
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,150
Slow down.

224
00:10:11,630 --> 00:10:13,270
What's the rush?

225
00:10:17,630 --> 00:10:19,550
I told you not to rush.

226
00:10:19,560 --> 00:10:22,000
If anything happened, she'd
be the one beating someone else up.

227
00:10:23,120 --> 00:10:25,320
She's been training in martial arts
since she was little.

228
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:42,790
Where did you get this?

229
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,030
St. Anton Hospital.

230
00:10:44,790 --> 00:10:45,550
What's in it?

231
00:10:48,030 --> 00:10:49,030
Blood fluke eggs.

232
00:10:49,030 --> 00:10:49,790
They're live eggs.

233
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:05,910
Chief Yuan.

234
00:11:06,510 --> 00:11:07,320
Young Master Zhao.

235
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:10,000
You got here later than I expected.

236
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:10,999
(Wu Tong, President
of St. Anto Hospital)

237
00:11:10,999 --> 00:11:13,630
Since you've been expecting us,
you must know why we're here.

238
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:16,270
Didn't your commissioner teach you

239
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:19,030
that you need evidence
before making an arrest?

240
00:11:19,720 --> 00:11:22,600
The first batch of drug trials
at St. Anto Hospital.

241
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:24,120
You gave the patients

242
00:11:24,510 --> 00:11:26,840
glucose water containing
blood fluke eggs.

243
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:37,150
They signed liability waivers.

244
00:11:37,150 --> 00:11:38,080
They took the money.

245
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,600
Life or death was on them.

246
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,760
You're treating human lives
like they're nothing.

247
00:11:41,770 --> 00:11:42,790
You call yourself a doctor?

248
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:45,440
Medical progress

249
00:11:45,630 --> 00:11:47,440
always requires sacrifices.

250
00:11:47,440 --> 00:11:49,910
If their lives help advance humanity,

251
00:11:50,630 --> 00:11:52,200
they should feel honored.

252
00:11:52,368 --> 00:11:54,420
Every year, countless people
along the Yangtze River

253
00:11:54,510 --> 00:11:57,120
are infected with blood flukes.

254
00:11:57,270 --> 00:11:58,150
It has a mortality rate

255
00:11:58,150 --> 00:12:00,000
as high as ninety percent.

256
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:02,120
Countless families
have been torn apart by it.

257
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:04,000
If my trials succeed,

258
00:12:04,976 --> 00:12:06,600
it won't be a terminal disease anymore.

259
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,390
But the disease is treatable.

260
00:12:08,870 --> 00:12:10,030
Wasn't it you who got the man

261
00:12:10,030 --> 00:12:11,000
who could treat it killed?

262
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:15,150
Gu Xishan was just lucky.

263
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:17,080
He knew nothing about parasites...

264
00:12:17,080 --> 00:12:18,910
I never even told you who that man was.

265
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:27,910
You killed Gu Xishan,

266
00:12:29,270 --> 00:12:30,910
and then set up
this pharmaceutical company

267
00:12:31,150 --> 00:12:33,270
to develop a cure for blood flukes.

268
00:12:33,270 --> 00:12:34,670
You were just waiting

269
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:35,840
for the day the disease spread,

270
00:12:35,840 --> 00:12:37,664
so you could profit
from a national disaster.

271
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:40,910
What a brilliant business plan.

272
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:46,670
You think

273
00:12:46,670 --> 00:12:48,240
this is my business alone?

274
00:12:48,660 --> 00:12:49,980
Go ahead and report me.

275
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:51,600
I'd like to see

276
00:12:52,550 --> 00:12:54,360
who you can actually bring down.

277
00:12:54,670 --> 00:12:55,630
Sounds like

278
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:56,750
you've got powerful people

279
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:58,200
backing you.

280
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:00,600
Let me ask you this.

281
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:02,030
Wu Shichuan's wife,

282
00:13:02,030 --> 00:13:03,200
the daughter of Minister Zhao.

283
00:13:03,910 --> 00:13:04,600
Is that enough

284
00:13:05,240 --> 00:13:06,960
for whoever's backing you

285
00:13:07,360 --> 00:13:08,960
to throw you under the bus?

286
00:13:39,320 --> 00:13:40,550
(The court hereby rules)

287
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:42,510
(that the defendant, Wu Tong,)

288
00:13:42,910 --> 00:13:44,750
(under the guise
of developing new medicine,)

289
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:46,510
(conducted human experiments,)

290
00:13:46,784 --> 00:13:49,240
(conspired with Director Wu Shichuan
of the Health Bureau,)

291
00:13:49,630 --> 00:13:51,440
(and framed the physician, Gu Xishan,)

292
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:53,440
(leading to his wrongful death
in prison.)

293
00:13:53,750 --> 00:13:55,000
(For multiple offenses,)

294
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:57,030
(he is sentenced
to ten years in prison,)

295
00:13:57,030 --> 00:13:58,910
(and all his property
is to be confiscated.)

296
00:14:00,980 --> 00:14:02,900
(Jingshi High Court)

297
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,232
The truth finally came to light,

298
00:14:09,264 --> 00:14:11,240
and the real culprit
was brought to justice.

299
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:13,000
It's all thanks to me, Zhao Shaoshang.

300
00:14:13,320 --> 00:14:14,480
And Chief Yuan.

301
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:16,840
The two of us joined forces,

302
00:14:17,120 --> 00:14:19,870
driven by our commitment to justice

303
00:14:19,870 --> 00:14:21,720
and our belief in the rule of law!

304
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:23,360
I believe that no matter who you are

305
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:25,080
or what your background is,

306
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:26,510
if you break the law,

307
00:14:26,510 --> 00:14:29,480
you'll be brought to justice.

308
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,440
Chief Yuan and I

309
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:33,720
are the dynamic duo of the police.

310
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:35,750
The guardian of justice.

311
00:14:35,750 --> 00:14:36,750
That's enough.

312
00:14:37,200 --> 00:14:37,600
All right.

313
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:38,910
That's all I have to say.

314
00:14:38,960 --> 00:14:39,960
Please take photos of us.

315
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:41,080
Come on. Look at that camera.

316
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:41,510
Come on.

317
00:15:02,360 --> 00:15:03,080
Sign it.

318
00:15:04,540 --> 00:15:07,740
(Divorcee: Zhao Wan'er)

319
00:15:12,910 --> 00:15:13,750
I don't have much time

320
00:15:14,840 --> 00:15:16,270
left anyway.

321
00:15:18,270 --> 00:15:20,120
Everything I own will be yours.

322
00:15:21,390 --> 00:15:22,510
Why do you

323
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:24,120
have to do this?

324
00:15:25,670 --> 00:15:26,960
I never wanted to marry you.

325
00:15:27,480 --> 00:15:28,480
My family forced me.

326
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,270
I told myself, "Forget it.

327
00:15:31,088 --> 00:15:32,440
It didn't matter who I married."

328
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,390
But I never imagined

329
00:15:34,928 --> 00:15:37,330
I'd be treated like a sinner
for not being able to have a child.

330
00:15:38,440 --> 00:15:40,240
You ruined people's lives for money.

331
00:15:40,240 --> 00:15:41,320
They came back for revenge,

332
00:15:41,670 --> 00:15:43,456
and your family blamed me for it.

333
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:45,670
The thought of being buried beside you

334
00:15:46,150 --> 00:15:47,630
after I die

335
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:49,720
makes me sick.

336
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:51,630
I'm determined

337
00:15:53,030 --> 00:15:54,000
to divorce you.

338
00:16:24,270 --> 00:16:24,870
Wu Shichuan,

339
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:26,840
you're under arrest.

340
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:28,480
Take him away.

341
00:16:28,736 --> 00:16:30,960
My family has served as officials
for three generations.

342
00:16:31,390 --> 00:16:33,150
You can't do this to me!

343
00:16:50,790 --> 00:16:52,510
What's got into you today, Young Master?

344
00:16:52,510 --> 00:16:53,510
You're up so early.

345
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:54,870
Don't ask.

346
00:16:58,870 --> 00:16:59,550
Father.

347
00:17:00,150 --> 00:17:00,750
Mother.

348
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:01,910
Morning, Shaoshang.

349
00:17:01,910 --> 00:17:02,550
Morning.

350
00:17:06,550 --> 00:17:08,550
Our son's done us proud.

351
00:17:10,070 --> 00:17:11,640
This first bowl of soup

352
00:17:12,960 --> 00:17:13,750
is for Shaoshang.

353
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:17,110
Take it.

354
00:17:17,110 --> 00:17:17,960
A reward for you.

355
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:19,920
Take it.

356
00:17:19,920 --> 00:17:20,720
Thank you, Mother.

357
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:23,720
Shaoshang,

358
00:17:24,680 --> 00:17:25,960
what do you think

359
00:17:25,960 --> 00:17:26,750
of Chief Yuan?

360
00:17:26,800 --> 00:17:28,192
Depends who you're comparing him to.

361
00:17:28,200 --> 00:17:29,910
If compared to me,
he's got a long way to go.

362
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:31,750
If compared to everyone else,
he's miles ahead.

363
00:17:31,960 --> 00:17:32,790
Really?

364
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,270
Do you think
he'd get along with her sister?

365
00:17:35,270 --> 00:17:36,400
Mom, I just got divorced.

366
00:17:36,480 --> 00:17:38,224
That's exactly why
we should start looking.

367
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,830
Hurry up.

368
00:17:43,200 --> 00:17:44,310
Hurry up.

369
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:51,860
(Young Detective Solves Bizarre Case)

370
00:17:54,030 --> 00:17:55,000
This is ridiculous!

371
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:56,070
That scoundrel!

372
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:57,070
What's wrong?

373
00:17:57,264 --> 00:17:59,640
I can't believe Yuan Hong
would pull something like this.

374
00:18:00,350 --> 00:18:01,920
Not one word about me
in the newspaper!

375
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,620
Without me, could
he have solved the case?

376
00:18:03,630 --> 00:18:05,830
And he wouldn't even have
known who the concubine was!

377
00:18:05,830 --> 00:18:08,160
And look this! "Underthe wise leadership
of the commissioner"?

378
00:18:08,170 --> 00:18:09,000
What's that old geezer

379
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,000
got to do with this case?

380
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,200
This is outrageous!

381
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:11,880
Uh...

382
00:18:12,830 --> 00:18:14,270
Maybe it's for the best.

383
00:18:14,750 --> 00:18:16,110
The case was too complicated.

384
00:18:16,110 --> 00:18:17,200
Being in the spotlight

385
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,510
might not be a good thing.

386
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:20,510
He used me, Father.

387
00:18:20,510 --> 00:18:21,488
First, he buttered me up,

388
00:18:21,490 --> 00:18:23,200
and then he tossed me
aside when he was done.

389
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:23,750
What am I?

390
00:18:23,750 --> 00:18:24,960
Disposable toilet paper?

391
00:18:25,110 --> 00:18:26,640
Stop being so hot-headed.

392
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:28,240
He's not someone
you want to mess with.

393
00:18:29,152 --> 00:18:30,440
Not someone I want to mess with?

394
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:32,000
Even emperors fall someday.

395
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:34,200
Not someone I want to mess
with? He started it!

396
00:18:37,030 --> 00:18:39,030
The police department created

397
00:18:39,030 --> 00:18:41,160
Division Four for him.

398
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:43,070
Why pick a fight with someone like that?

399
00:18:43,310 --> 00:18:44,240
What a snake.

400
00:18:44,680 --> 00:18:45,920
Two-faced.

401
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:46,896
I'm not letting this go!

402
00:18:46,912 --> 00:18:50,420
(End of Episode 4)

403
00:18:50,601 --> 00:18:52,241
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

404
00:18:52,241 --> 00:18:53,781
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

405
00:18:53,781 --> 00:18:55,031
♪However, the world changes♪

406
00:18:55,031 --> 00:18:56,951
♪You'll still be by my side♪

407
00:18:56,951 --> 00:18:58,641
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

408
00:18:58,641 --> 00:19:00,211
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

409
00:19:00,211 --> 00:19:01,781
♪If this is my final chapter♪

410
00:19:01,781 --> 00:19:04,281
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
